--- !u!114 &1212945551
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1212945549}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: f4688fdb7df04437aeb418b961361dc5, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "<size=24>Moving Through the Dungeon<size=14>\n\nYou may <u><b>run</b></u>
    from a room if it seems too dangerous. \n\nThe cards in the room get placed back
    on the bottom of the deck.\n\r\nRunning has a cooldown of one room, meaning you
    <u>must</u> fight the next room. \nUnless you have extra <b>run tokens</b>, in
    which case you can spend a token to run when you normally couldn't\r\n\r\nYou
    may leave a room when a room is down to:\n   - Its last card\n   - No cards\n  
    - <u>Only one card and just door cards remain</u>\n\r\nIf the room still has
    a card in it when you go into the next, that card continues into the next room.
    \nExcept doors, which are shuffled back in.\n\n\n<size=24>Advancing<size=14>\n\nDoors
    require a certain number of <u>points</u> to use. You may see the point value
    needed by hovering over a door.\n\nIn between floors of the dungeon you can choose
    to heal or upgrade either yourself or your cards.\n\n<size=24>Other<size=14>\n\nYou
    may find treasure cards in the dungeon. These grant 3 gold and do nothing else."
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 75264fa9e13da2b41919fefa895e40a6, type: 2}
  m_sharedMaterial: {fileID: 255578546575997133, guid: 75264fa9e13da2b41919fefa895e40a6, type: 2}
